turba2 (2.2.1-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release. 
  * The main changes compared to the previous version: Unescaped output in the
    contact view has been fixed. Importing of phone numbers has been
    improved. The upgrade script has been fixed.
  * No more need to copy CREDITS file in debian/rules. 
  * Update to standards version 3.8.0, no further required changes. 
  * Link some *.js files with libjs-scriptaculous package. 
  * Improvements in debian/copyright file. 

 -- Gregory Colpart (evolix) <reg@evolix.fr>  Sun, 15 Jun 2008 16:21:53 +0200

turba2 (2.1.7-1) unstable; urgency=high

  * New upstream release.
  * This release adds restrictions to ensure you can't edit another user's
    contact in the same SQL backend table if you guess the id. (Closes:
    #464058).
  * Use now Vcs-* fields in debian/control.
  * Put the CREDITS file where the online help viewer expects it (See
    #357377).
  * Update to standards version 3.7.3, no further required changes.
  * Bump debhelper compat level to 5.
  * Add Homepage field.

 -- Gregory Colpart (evolix) <reg@evolix.fr>  Sat, 16 Feb 2008 22:12:25 +0100

turba2 (2.1.4-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * New upstream release.
  * Transition to PHP5 for Recommends and Suggests fields. (Closes: #432244)
  * Add php-net-ldap in Suggests: (Closes: #366623)
  * Remove Jose Carlos Medeiros from Uploaders:
  * Remove exec right for XML files in debian/rules.
  * Remove LICENSE file (already in debian/copyright) to fix a lintian
    warning.
  * Exclude INSTALL file when dh_installdocs to fix a lintian warning.
  * Cleaning binary-arch target to be coherent with others horde packages.
  * Added XS-VCS-* fields in debian/control. 

